Croup is a condition that affects mostly children under the age of five, but can affect older individuals as well.

It is an inflammation of the bronchial, larynx, also known as the respiratory tract.
'''
Treatment'''
Home treatment generally is best for croup, although parents who are concerned are urged to contact their doctor immediately.

Most cases of croup are mild, but severe cases may require hospitalization.

'''Symptoms'''
A barking cough, a wheezing sound, and labored breathing are all common with croup. The condition usually lasts for several days, but can last for weeks in severe cases.